JSE-listed gold miner Harmony Gold Mining Company, with operations in Gauteng, the North West and the Free State, as well as in Papua New Guinea, has appointed Peter Turner as a new member of its investment committee, effective May 7. Prior to this, Turner had also been appointed as an independent nonexecutive director and a technical committee member with effect from February 19. Harmony chairperson Dr Patrice Motsepe says Turnerâ€™s extensive experience in openpit and deep-level underground gold mining operations in Africa will make a significant contribution to the technical expertise required for the safety initiatives, development and growth of the company.